    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nRunning `systemlist` with a command that expects input from `stdin` prepends the following error messages to the output:\r\n\r\n```\r\nerror: Unable to read input file: Is a directory\r\nsource: Error while reading file '<stdin>'\r\nerror: Unable to read input file: Is a directory\r\nsource: Error while reading file '<stdin>'\r\n```\r\n\r\nI initially encountered this when [formatting](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/b7782daacebf8842bece6e41a20ee9a4859721e6/runtime/autoload/zig/fmt.vim#L31) a Zig file, though it seems to be a general problem, as the same behaviour is reproducible with `cat`.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean --cmd 'echo systemlist(\"cat\", bufnr(\"\"))'\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNo errors in the returned output\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev-19+g0f4f7d32c and v0.10.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim version 9.0.2018\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 14.2.1 (23C71)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.32.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nscreen-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nBrew and build from source",
